results.occurrenceRemarks: I found Whip-poor-will and Chuck-will's-widow singing together. I also heard Eastern Screech Owl in the background.  The recording starts with Whip-poor-will, then Chuck-will's-widow joins. The Whip-poor-will stops and the Chuck-will's-widow continues.

results.occurrenceRemarks: I was leading a birding tour at the time of this photo and didn't take the time to properly photograph this road-killed nightjar.  I *think* it is a female Eastern Whip-poor-will but it's hard to judge such things as tail length and crown striping in this single image.
